				<p><p>RANSAC is usually used to segment planes from the point cloud (see: <a href="http://www.pointclouds.org/documentation/tutorials/planar_segmentation.php" rel="nofollow">http://www.pointclouds.org/documentation/tutorials/planar_segmentation.php</a>). </p>

<p>As an alternative, when you detect objects that are on the road you could neglect surfaces/points for which the curvature is close or equal to zero. However, this requires you to have some way to get the curvature information, for example, normals (see: <a href="http://pointclouds.org/documentation/tutorials/normal_estimation.php" rel="nofollow">http://pointclouds.org/documentation/tutorials/normal_estimation.php</a>).</p>
